data.title: Sales
data.tip: Sales = Gross Sales - Discounts + Taxes + Shipping (i.e. what the customer paid for shipping)

data.title: New Customer Revenue
data.tip: New Customer Revenue = Amount of Sales derived from New Customers

data.title: Net Sales
data.tip: Net Sales = Sales - Refunds (Note: Sales is as defined in our Sales metric)

data.title: Returning Customer Revenue
data.tip: Returning Customer Revenue = Amount of Sales derived from Returning Customers

data.title: Payment Gateways
data.tip: Payment Gateways = Payment processing fees. Edit these in: Store > Gateway Costs

data.title: COGS
data.tip: COGS = Cost of Goods Sold. Imported from Shopify, or edit these in: Store > Cost of Goods

data.title: Handling Fees
data.tip: Handling Fees = Cost of boxing, packaging, or “pick & pack” services. Edit these in: Store > Cost of Goods

data.title: Custom Expenses
data.tip: Custom Expenses = Any additional expenses you'd like to see deducted from your Net Profit. Edit these in: Store > Custom Expenses

data.title: Items
data.tip: Number of total items you have in stock.

data.title: Missing Items
data.tip: Missing Items = number of back order items.

data.title: Cost
data.tip: How much did the items cost.

data.title: Value
data.tip: Value = retail value of items in stock.

data.title: AOV
data.tip: AOV (Average Order Value) = Sales / Orders>$0

data.title: AOV
data.tip: Google Analytics reported average order value.

data.title: Facebook Ads
data.tip: Ads = ad spend.

data.title: Google Ads
data.tip: Ads = Google ad spend.

data.title: Google CPA
data.tip: CPA = cost per purchase.

data.title: Bounce Rate
data.tip: Bounce Rate = percentage of visitors to the website that leave before any action or visiting other pages.

data.title: Google Conversion Value
data.tip: Conversion Value = recorded revenue from Google ads.

data.title: Snapchat Ads
data.tip: Ads = Snapchat ad spend.

data.title: Snapchat ROAS
data.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

data.title: Conversion Rate
data.tip: Google Analytics reported conversion rate.

data.title: Net Profit
data.tip: Net Profit = Sales - Returns - Expenses (COGS, Shipping, Handling, Payment Gateways, Taxes, Custom Expenses) - Blended Ad Spend.

data.title: Cash Turnover
data.tip: Cash Turnover = Sales - Shipping - Taxes - Blended Ad Spend - Returns.

data.title: Net Margin
data.tip: Net Margin = Net Profit / Sales x 100. In other words: Percentage of Sales that is Net Profit. Answers the question of: “What percentage of my [Sales] is my [Net Profit]?”

data.title: Blended CPA
data.tip: Cost Per Acquisition is Ad spend/Google Analytics Transaction.

data.title: RPS
data.tip: RPS (Revenue Per Session) = Sales / Web Sessions.

data.title: Refunds
data.tip: Refunds = The amount refunded during the selected timeframe. Note that the refunded amount applies on the refund date, not on the original date of sale. Triple Whale may not match Shopify on a day-to-day basis.

data.title: Facebook ROAS
data.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

data.title: Google ROAS
data.tip: ROAS = return on ad spend.

data.title: Google CTR
data.tip: CTR = percentage of people clicking the ad.

data.title: Google CPM
data.tip: CPM = cost per 1000 impressions.

data.title: Google CPC
data.tip: CPC = cost per click.

data.title: Google All CPA
data.tip: All CPA = cost per all conversions.

data.title: Facebook CPC
data.tip: CPC = cost per click.

data.title: Facebook View Conversion Value
data.tip: VCV = Facebook View Conversion Value

data.title: Facebook View ROAS

data.title: Facebook Meta Conversion Value
data.tip: Meta Conversion Value = Facebook-reported revenue from Purchases on Meta Shop

data.title: Revenue Per Link Click
data.tip: Revenue per link click = Conversion value / Out bound clicks.

data.title: Facebook CPA
data.tip: CPA = cost per purchase (Approx).

data.title: Purchases
data.tip: Purchases - Orders made on your site or on Meta Shop

data.title: Meta Purchases
data.tip: Meta Purchases - Orders made on Meta Shop

data.title: Web Purchases
data.tip: Web Purchases - Orders made on your site

data.title: New Customers CPA
data.tip: NCPA (New Customer Cost Per Acquisition) = Total Ad Spend / New Customers.

data.title: Email Open Rate
data.tip: Email Open Rate = received emails / opened emails. On a one day view this metric is off and in general TripleWhale's number does not match Klaviyo's number.

data.title: CVR
data.tip: Purchase number / Received Emails

data.title: Revenue Per Email
data.tip: Sales / Received Emails

data.title: LTV
data.tip: LTV (Lifetime Value) = Sales / Unique Customers

data.title: Frequency
data.tip: Frequency = The average number of times Unique Customers place a purchase.

data.title: LTV/CPA
data.tip: LTV/CPA = Lifetime Value / Cost Per Acquisition

data.title: MER
data.tip: MER (Marketing Efficiency Ratio) = Percentage of Sales spent on Ads.

data.title: Returns %
data.tip: Returns % = Refunds / Sales. The percentage of your returns relative to your sales.

data.title: Orders
data.tip: Orders = Number of Orders within the selected timeframe

data.title: Taxes
data.tip: Taxes = Amount customers paid in taxes (not including shipping taxes).

data.title: New Customers
data.tip: New Customers = Percentage of orders placed by New Customers

data.title: Returning Customers
data.tip: Returning Customers = Percentage of orders placed by Returning Customers

data.title: New Customer Orders
data.tip: New Customers = Number of orders placed by New Customers

data.title: Unique Customers
data.tip: Unique Customers = Number of Unique Customers within the selected timeframe

data.title: Shipping
data.tip: Shipping = Amount the store paid in shipping costs for fulfilling orders within the select timeframe. Edit these in: Store > Shipping

data.title: Items Sold
data.tip: Items Sold = Number of items sold within the selected timeframe

data.title: Blended Ad Spend
data.tip: Blended Ad Spend = Total Ad Spend. This includes the reported ad spend of each marketing channel connected to Triple Whale, plus any Custom Expenses marked as Ad Spend.

data.title: Blended ROAS
data.tip: Blended ROAS (Return on Ad Spend) = Sales / Blended Ads.

data.title: New Customer ROAS
data.tip: New Customer ROAS (Return on Ad Spend) = Sales from New Customers / Blended Ad Spend.

data.title: Blended Attributed ROAS
data.tip: BA ROAS (Blended-Attributed ROAS) = Total Blended Conversion Value (reported by each marketing channel) / Blended Ad Spend

data.title: Profit on Ad Spend
data.tip: POAS is Gross-Profit/Total-Ad-spend.

data.title: Blended CPA
data.tip: CPA (Cost Per Acquisition) = Blended Ad Spend / Orders > $0

data.title: Finance Cash Total
data.tip: The total amount of cash across all your business bank accounts at the end of this time period.

data.title: Finance Credit Total
data.tip: The total outstanding balance across all your business credit cards at the end of this time period.

data.title: Money In
data.tip: The total amount of cash that came into your business bank account(s) during this time period.

data.title: Money Out
data.tip: The total amount of cash that left your business bank account(s) during this time period.

data.title: Beginning Cash
data.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the end of this time period.

data.title: Ending Cash
data.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the beginning of this time period.

data.title: Total Change
data.tip: The difference between the amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the beginning and end of this period.

data.tip: The total amount of cash you had in your business bank account(s) at the end of this time period.

data.title: Credit Card Debt
data.tip: The total amount of credit card debt you had at the end of this time period.

data.title: Invoices Total
data.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices.

data.title: Total Due within 30 Days
data.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 30 days from now.

data.title: Total Due within 60 Days
data.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 60 days from now.

data.title: Total Due within 90 Days
data.tip: This represents the total amount that you need to pay across all your invoices between now and 90 days from now.

data.title: EBITDA
data.tip: Earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization.

data.title: Burn Rate
data.tip: The amount of money your business lost during this time period, net of all expenses

data.title: Runway (Days)
data.tip: The amount of time you have before your business run out of cash (assuming no change in funding or business performance).

data.title: Valuation
data.tip: The value of your business.  Click this tile to edit the formula for valuation.

data.title: Average Daily Sales
data.tip: The amount of revenue your business generates on a typical day.
